        <h1>OAuth</h1>
        <ul>
            <li>What Is It?</li>
            <p>
                It stands for Open Authorization and it is one approach to authenticating users inside our application.
                (other options JsonWebTokens, Hawk?.)
            </p>
            <p>
                Basically, it allows users to log into our app using 3rd party services such as Facebook, Google,
                GitHub or LinkedIn or one of our social profiles if we have one.
            </p>
            <li>Why use it?</li>
            <p>One less thing to worry about as a developer. </p>

            <p>And for users</p>
            Users may find it easier because they can just use a username and password that they already have.
            <p>Instead of filling out a form and remembering a new username and password</p>
            <p>And maybe people just prefer using a few central identities like facebook or google so that they can
                login anywhere.</p>
        </ul>
